{
  "text": "Our approach is designed to work without explicit background subtraction. In outdoor settings with moving backgrounds and uncontrolled illumination, such segmentation is hard, but progress has been made by multi-view segmentation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , joint segmentation and reconstruction [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] , and also aided by propagation of a manual initialization [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . However, the obtained segmentations are still noisy, enabling only rather coarse 3D reconstructions [CITATION_10] , and many methods would not work with only two cameras.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5694118",
    "[CITATION_2]": "1206295",
    "[CITATION_3]": "8600256",
